PY  - 2020
T2  - International Journal of Radiation Research
VL  - 18
IS  - 2
SP  - 375
EP  - 380
DO  - 10.18869/acadpub.ijrr.18.2.375
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-85089186482&doi=10.18869%2Facadpub.ijrr.18.2.375&partnerID=40&md5=02ecb3e08432e00aca671f24396ef0aa
AB  - Background: Endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography (ERCP) is now widely used in the diagnosis and treatment of gastrointestnal tract disorders. A large number of X-ray fluoroscopy and digital radiographs make ERCP as an interventonal radiological procedure. In this study, patents' and examiner's entrance skin doses (ESDs) were measured during diagnosis and treatment procedures and patents' effectve dose (ED) were calculated. Materials and Methods: Thermoluminescent dosimeters (TLDs) and dose area product meter (DAP) were used to measure ESDs of 30 patents and examiner and calculate patents' ED. Besides, to assess the effectveness of an extra lead shield in decreasing examiner's ESDs, a lead cover was wrapped around the X-ray tube. The data were analyzed with IBM SPSS Statstcs version 16 software. Results: The mean DAP and fluoroscopy tme (FT) of the diagnostc procedure were 4.09 Gy.cm2and 32.4 s while those of the therapeutc procedure were 7.60 Gy.cm2and 76.2 s. The strong linear correlaton between DAP and FT was observed for the therapeutc procedures but the diagnostc ones. The patents' mean EDs of diagnostc procedure (1.21±0.52 mSv) and therapeutc one (2.25±1.72 mSv) were calculated. Moreover, the shielding cover around the X-ray tube decreased ESDs of the organs of interest except gonads. Conclusions: The results reveal that therapeutc ERCP procedure imposes a greater radiaton dose compared to diagnostc ERCP one. However, the doses of the patent and the examiner depend highly on examiner's experience, technical skills and knowledge in radiaton protecton. The results suggest that atempts to reduce radiaton doses should be made. © 2020 Novin Medical Radiation Institute. All rights reserved.
